The paper proposes a method for learning compact representations of motor sequences that capture the structure of resulting displacements. This involves using Recurrent Neural Networks to encode motor sequences and predict the consequence of motor sequences in terms of sensory changes. The paper also discusses the organization of these representations in terms of spatial displacement. Given these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
